Enterprise: Enterprise customers sign

5
00:00:08,460 --> 00:00:09,900
an enterprise agreement with Azure,

6
00:00:09,900 --> 00:00:11,070
that commits them to spending

7
00:00:11,070 --> 00:00:13,290
a negotiated amount
on Azure services,

8
00:00:13,290 --> 00:00:15,090
which they typically pay annually.

9
00:00:15,090 --> 00:00:19,290
Enterprise customers also have
access to customized Azure pricing.

10
00:00:19,290 --> 00:00:21,810
Web direct: Web direct customers

11
00:00:21,810 --> 00:00:23,985
sign up for Azure, through
the Azure website.

12
00:00:23,985 --> 00:00:26,340
Web direct customers pay
the same prices that the

13
00:00:26,340 --> 00:00:28,620
general public pay
for Azure resources,

14
00:00:28,620 --> 00:00:29,820
and their monthly billing and

15
00:00:29,820 --> 00:00:32,325
payments occur through
the Azure website.

16
00:00:32,325 --> 00:00:36,810
Cloud Service Provider:
Cloud Service Providers, CSPs,

17
00:00:36,810 --> 00:00:39,330
typically are Microsoft
partner companies that

18
00:00:39,330 --> 00:00:41,940
a customer hires to bill
solutions on top of Azure.

19
00:00:41,940 --> 00:00:43,685
Payment and billing for Azure usage

20
00:00:43,685 --> 00:00:46,350
occurs through the Customer CSP.

21
00:00:47,050 --> 00:00:50,405
Products and services in Azure
are arranged by category,

22
00:00:50,405 --> 00:00:52,775
which have various resources
that you can provision.

23
00:00:52,775 --> 00:00:54,290
You select the Azure products and

24
00:00:54,290 --> 00:00:55,955
services that fit your requirements,

25
00:00:55,955 --> 00:00:57,710
and your account is billed according

26
00:00:57,710 --> 00:01:00,420
to the Azure consumption-based model.

27
00:01:01,340 --> 00:01:03,945
When you provision an Azure resource,

28
00:01:03,945 --> 00:01:07,145
Azure creates one or more meter
instances for that resource.

29
00:01:07,145 --> 00:01:09,335
The meters track the resources usage,

30
00:01:09,335 --> 00:01:10,550
and each meter generates

31
00:01:10,550 --> 00:01:13,430
a usage record that is used
to calculate your bill.

32
00:01:13,430 --> 00:01:17,180
For example, a single virtual
machine that you provision in Azure,

33
00:01:17,180 --> 00:01:19,010
might have some of
the following meters tracking

34
00:01:19,010 --> 00:01:21,230
its usage: Compute hours,

35
00:01:21,230 --> 00:01:24,275
IP address hours, data transfer in,

36
00:01:24,275 --> 00:01:27,225
data transfer out, and others.

37
00:01:27,225 --> 00:01:29,160
An Azure free account provide

38
